cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper deals with the task of semantic scene labeling for autonomous driving using deep neural networks. This task involves processing 3D point sets obtained from sensors like LiDAR and Radar. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper focuses on autonomous driving, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The proposed methodology involves re-weighting the loss function based on class frequencies, which is a common technique in machine learning and could place the paper in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses transfer learning, which is a popular technique in deep learning and could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
